Nvidia shares fell in after-hours trading as the chipmaker’s revenue forecast fell short of thehighestanalyst estimates. Third-quarter revenue will be about $32.5 billion — that beat the average analyst estimate of $31.9 billion  butsome rangedas high as $37.9 billion. That overshadowed the company’s announcement for an additional $50 billion share buyback  as well as data-center revenue that exceeded estimates.
